{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Virizion}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=639|prev=Terrakion|nextnum=641|next=Tornadus|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Virizion}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Virizion\n|jname=ビリジオン\n|jtranslit=Birujion\n|tmname=Virizion\n|category=Grassland\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Grass\n|type2=Fighting\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Justified\n|ndex=640\n|udex=146\n|u2dex=227\n|height-ftin=6\'07"\n|height-m=2.0\n|weight-lbs=440.9\n|weight-kg=200.0\n|egggroupn=0\n|egggroup1=Undiscovered\n|eggcycles=80\n|expyield=261\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=255\n|color=Green\n|evtotal=3\n|evsd=3\n|catchrate=3\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=virizion\n|generation=5\n|friendship=35\n}}\n\'\'\'Virizion\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ビリジオン\'\'\' \'\'Virizion\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Grass|Fighting}} [[Legendary Pokémon]] introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any Pokémon.\n\nAlong with {{p|Cobalion}}, {{p|Terrakion}}, and {{p|Keldeo}}, Virizion is a member of the [[Swords of Justice]].\n\n==Biology==\nVirizion is a stag or {{wp|antelope}}-like, quadruped Pokémon that is primarily green. On the sides of its head are long horns that end in dull, curled points. It has a pointed snout with a black blaze running from its nose to the back of its head. Its face, hind legs, and underside are white. There is a pinked-tipped leaf on each side of its neck, and leafy tufts on its shoulders. On its back, there are pointed tufts of fur forming a medium-long tail. Its lower legs resemble knee-high boots with pink highlights at the knees, and it has black hooves.\n\nLike the other members of [[Swords of Justice|its quartet]], Virizion battled against humans in order to protect Pokémon. Its horns are as sharp as blades, and are used to cut opponents.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Virizion M15.png|thumb|250px|left|Virizion in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n===={{DL|Swords of Justice (M15)|Virizion|Virizion (M15)}}====\nVirizion debuted in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\', being one of its stars alongside {{p|Cobalion}}, {{p|Terrakion}}, {{OBP|Kyurem|M15}}, and {{OBP|Keldeo|M15}}. Along with Cobalion, Terrakion, Keldeo, and Kyurem, Virizion can [[Talking Pokémon|speak through telepathy]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[File:Virizion Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Virizion in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n{{main|Swords of Justice (Adventures)}}\nVirizion was the first of the Swords of Justice to debut in Pokémon Adventures, appearing in \'\'[[PS476|A Direct Attack and a Daunting Defense]]\'\', where it attacks {{adv|Black}} and {{adv|White}} as they cross the [[Skyarrow Bridge]], cutting up their clothing. Virizion later appears alongside Terrakion in [[Mistralton Cave]]. Both would later follow Cobalion to [[Pledge Grove]] to meet [[Kelden|Keldeo]].\n\n===In the Be the Best! Pokémon B+W manga===\n[[Monta]] owns a Virizion, which he uses in an attempt to weaken {{p|Kyurem}}.\n\n===In the Pokémon RéBURST manga===\nVirizion, along with Cobalion and Terrakion, were captured by [[Great Gavel]] via holding several Pokémon captive. Later, it was sealed into a Burst Heart and became the [[Burst]] form of [[Rovy]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Virizion (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n{{spoilers}}\n{{main|Virizion (Gates to Infinity)}}\n[[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Gates to Infinity]]: {{mdc|Virizion|gti}} is a very popular Pokémon among the [[Post Town]] inhabitants, even though she has turned them all down at some point. The {{player}} first meets her after rescuing {{mdc|Dunsparce|gti}}. Dunsparce had gotten lost looking for a crystal to give to Virizion as a gift, because he wanted to be her friend. Virizion turns him down, saying she doesn\'t have friends. This hurts Dunsparce\'s feelings, causing him to run away. After rescuing Dunsparce again, she asks to join the team. The player\'s partner immediately accepts, much to {{mdc|Emolga|gti}}\'s chagrin. Virizion proves to be a calm and collected addition to the team, rarely outwardly expressing her emotions, but she changes as more and more is revealed about her past with her last friend, {{mdc|Keldeo|gti}}. She later admits that she likes Emolga.\n{{endspoilers}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=grass|type2=fighting}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=146|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=227|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=fff|entry=Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=grass|type2=fighting}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|area=[[Pinwheel Forest]] <small>(Ruminatio